(181, 1, '2015-05-12 19:42:03', '2015-05-12 19:42:03', '<h2><b>Key Facts</b></h2>\r\n<b>Locations: </b>Corporate HQ in Pittsburgh, PA, and retail stores worldwide\r\n\r\n<b>Industry: </b>Retail - Youth Apparel\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><b>The Word </b><b> </b></h2>\r\n<b>From the Project Manager to our UI Developer </b>\r\n<blockquote>I had been fighting for these changes for five months! It was our biggest pain point for our call centers...every day they complain about it. You have saved the day!</blockquote>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><b>The challenge</b></h2>\r\nWhat can be done without an experienced UI team? Not much of anything, really. But Our client needed UI improvements that supported their plans for global expansion, and they had their eyes on the UK and needed their website to truly represent them as a company. The last code written for the website dated back to 2008, with most of it written years before. We stepped in to give them the UI guidance they needed to take their website to the next level. In order for the UI to support their expansion plans, there were serious updates needed to be done for the CSR Application too:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Currency conversion for international business</li>\r\n	<li>Complete website redesign</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><b>The Journey</b></h2>\r\n<b>Currency conversion for international business</b>\r\n\r\nOur client’s internal e-commerce system only supported currency conversions that either went to or from US dollars. So for those ordering from the UK but using Euros, there was no hope other than to use 3rd party online tools. We designed a module that had the intelligence to call internal API’s to convert the foreign currencies to other foreign currencies without the customer have to worry about using US dollars. This CSR app supports anywhere between 300 or 400 customer representatives at a time, so it needed to be nimble. This module created the workaround by using AJAX, which detected which currency the user was coming from and going to simply by pinging the server, and then created a new, appropriate currency conversion rate based on the information it found on the web.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Complete website redesign</b>\r\n\r\nThere hadn’t been any new UI enhancements added to the website since 2008...and it was obvious. The site needed a serious facelift. It was created in a time when adaptive/responsive design frameworks didn’t exist and IE7 was considered cutting edge - yikes! We dusted the cobwebs off the code, and set to work. For starters, we created a login screen that used modern AJAX &amp; CSS3 for the login screen which communicated errors via animations. Then we created a bulletin board which allowed messages to be left for employees which kept them up to date on news. We integrated social media as well, which helped customer service reps know what was going on in real time, catch any issues before they bubbled over, and gave them insight which created a true sense of empathy. This improved their customer support success and customers were overjoyed.', 'Fortune 1000 Retailer', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '175-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-05-12 19:42:03', '2015-05-12 19:42:03', '', 175, 'http://revamp.avenuecode.com/175-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
