(208, 1, '2015-05-12 19:54:35', '2015-05-12 19:54:35', 'At Avenue Code, we believe it´s very important to do charity work. Not only does it help those in need, but in our experience, it also strengthens the team spirit and camaraderie between Avenue Code team members.\r\n\r\nThis Christmas, Sabrina at our Belo office, had the idea to do an event in a home for the elderly. This is her story:\r\n<h2>The Beginning</h2>\r\nI chatted with my friends from Avenue Code and it really started to generate a buzz. People loved the idea. I researched several elderly shelters and retirement houses and wanted to find one which housed both men and women. In addition, I wanted to give to one that had the largest need. The one I found survived mostly on donations, and housed all genders...we decided to volunteer at the Geriatric Institute Afonso Pena (Igap). I asked the Avenue Coders to help me raise funds to make the event happen. We would need a large sum  to accomplish what we had planned at the end; luckily for us, we were able to surpass our fundraising goal!\r\n\r\n<a href="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/10428062_881662908534512_8877249243752155384_n.jpg"><img class="alignleft wp-image-573 " src="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/10428062_881662908534512_8877249243752155384_n-300x225.jpg" alt="10428062_881662908534512_8877249243752155384_n" width="263" height="197" /></a>\r\n\r\nWith the money we raised, we were able to donate to the institution many geriatric toiletry items, individual presents for each elder, as well as flowers. The event took place in the morning December 10th, and had the participation of many Avenue Code team members. I can say that their participation was amazing, and very touching. Last but not least, we also had the special contribution of the Real Life English team. Thanks everyone!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>The Arrival<img class="alignleft wp-image-576 size-medium" src="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/1912129_881664205201049_5304715791000311047_n-300x225.jpg" alt="1912129_881664205201049_5304715791000311047_n" width="300" height="225" /></h2>\r\nUpon arrival on site, we came across many elderly sitting on the door sunbathing and observing people passing on the street. Upon entering, we were very well received by the staff and primarily by the elderly folks. The Institute houses a total of 26 elderly women and 15 men, who are supported not only donations, but also a lot of warmth and affection. During our stay at the place, we had the opportunity to talk to all of them, share hugs, laughs, stories, and light hearted feelings. In addition, we distributed gifts and flowers to each of them, which made them very happy and surprised! To top it off, we hired a medieval performance group, who sang some Christmas songs and read Alysson´s message, which was very moving. All the employees at the Institute were cheered up the presentation, and thanked us for our visit.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Saying Goodbye<img class="alignleft wp-image-577 size-medium" src="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/10357609_881667608534042_144205032015619257_n-300x225.jpg" alt="10357609_881667608534042_144205032015619257_n" width="300" height="225" /></h2>\r\nIt was quite hard to say goodbye to the elderly, they asked anxiously if we\'d come back the next day, and tried not to cry...I\'m sure several Avenue Coders had the same feeling. Finally, we gave them a warm hug with the promise that we\'d be back soon. The experience of this event was truly amazing! Most people always remember the children but may end up forgetting about the elderly, who are highly in need of human care, a good talk, and a good listener. We were happy we could provide them the attention they so deserved. Surely, we will return several times in the shelter of the elderly.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class="size-medium wp-image-575 alignleft" src="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/1458458_881663725201097_5632140107454503655_n-300x225.jpg" alt="1458458_881663725201097_5632140107454503655_n" width="300" height="225" />', 'Tis\' the Season To Give Back', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '200-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-05-12 19:54:35', '2015-05-12 19:54:35', '', 200, 'http://revamp.avenuecode.com/200-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(209, 1, '2014-12-04 21:48:20', '2014-12-04 21:48:20', 'Now that this year is coming to fast close, it’s time to look ahead and prepare for how front-end design trends have grown and changed. We talked to our talented team of engineers and asked them what they believe their top front-end developer trends are for 2015.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><b>Compatibility </b></h2>\r\n<h3><i>AngularJS, BackboneJS, React are still going strong.</i></h3>\r\nJavascript frameworks - such as <b>AngularJS, Backbone.js </b>and <b>React </b>- have reached a new stability level,  and cross-browser compatibility has developed in such a way that it\'s no longer a risk to implement JS based applications. Before, cross-browser compatibility used to prevent big corporations from adopting those frameworks, as they usually had to support a lot of old browsers. Nowadays, frameworks have better support for multiple browsers (and most of them are still supporting really old ones like IE7, IE8). As a result, they are being used more by big players in the market. That\'s a trend we can see with most of our clients at Avenue Code.\r\n<h2><b>Web Components</b></h2>\r\n<h3><i>libraries agree - components are awesome!</i></h3>\r\nWeb Components will become even more important in 2015 because it will turn front-end development inside out. Web Components greatly simplifies how UI components are developed, by favoring reuse and sharing component-specific knowledge. It will trend because of the increasing focus on the "web componentizing" approach advocated by libraries such as <b>React</b>, which forces the developer to define the web application as a tree of fully-featured components. Besides that, there has been a big progress leap with the specification of Web Components, which is being widely promoted by libraries such as <b>Polymer </b>and <b>X-Tags</b>.\r\n\r\nWeb Components are awesome because it directly attacks the current number of development challenges - such as code repetition, bad cohesion, poor coupling, inability to reuse the component in different contexts, and lack of testing and certification by the community, which essentially forces one to reinvent the wheel each time. Web Components will provide a productivity boom for the front-end development world.\r\n<h2><b><a href="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Mobile-1.png">\r\n</a><a href="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Mobile-1.png"><img class="alignleft wp-image-562 size-medium" src="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Mobile-1-212x300.png" alt="" width="212" height="300" /></a></b><b></b></h2>\r\n<h2><b>Mobile-first Design</b></h2>\r\n<h3><i>Consumers can be found on their phones, we must adjust accordingly!</i></h3>\r\nMobile-first design should lead development methods due to responsive design techniques maturedness. Mobile device usage has exploded, and creative teams should explore newer features (e.g. geolocation, touch) in order to define unique experiences like real-time trackers, local-based content, etc.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2></h2>\r\n<h2></h2>\r\n<h2><b><img class="alignleft wp-image-563 size-medium" src="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Untitled-design-200x300.png" alt="Untitled design" width="200" height="300" />User Experience</b></h2>\r\n<h3><i>Natural design will still be king.</i></h3>\r\nNext year’s UX trends will take advantage of some natural (intuitive) gestures provided by the mobile devices themselves (especially swiping and scrolling). As a direct result, there should be more usage of content in a single page instead of the user having to click on multiple links to find what he or she is looking for.\r\n\r\nThe cool thing about these three trends is that they converge to provide a faster, more intuitive, and cleaner web experience that stays consistent regardless of when a user switches from one device to another. Lastly, community will continue to be a large part of front-end design, specifically with web components.\r\nLooks like the theme for 2015 is beautifully simple and stable front-end design and development. We aim to do more with less...looks like everyone else will too in the new year.', 'Front-end Design Trends for 2015', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'front-end-design-trends-for-2015', '', '', '2015-05-18 17:14:57', '2015-05-18 17:14:57', '', 0, 'http://revamp.avenuecode.com/?p=209', 0, 'post', '', 0) ;
