="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-432" style="width: 540px !important;" src="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/qunit.png" alt="qunit" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><b>Mocking Tools</b></h3>\r\nWhile it’s important to make everything work together, it’s also important to make sure every component can work properly when independently deployed. That’s why we need options to mock data or requests and simulate communication with other parties and assert our code behaves to all possible situations. The best part of this is that we can even simulate communication failures!\r\n<h3><b>Browsers / Automated tasks</b></h3>\r\nWe all know how boring it is to keep doing the same tests in different browsers. Why waste our time on these repetitive tasks when we can automate and let our machine do all the work for us?\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-448" src="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/test-diagram.png" alt="test-diagram" width="552" height="480" /></p>', 'Front-end tests: Yes we can!', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '221-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-05-12 20:31:27', '2015-05-12 20:31:27', '', 221, 'http://revamp.avenuecode.com/221-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
