(255, 1, '2012-12-12 21:33:17', '2012-12-12 21:33:17', 'It\'s Christmas, and through the great magic that surrounds this time of year, it awakens within us the potential for solidarity and compassion, it refills our spirit with hope in humanity and generosity - giving back.\r\n\r\nAnd with this spirit, the Avenue Code is organizing a charity campaign to help Daycare in an underprivileged neighborhood Creche Terra Nova, Brazil. Every day there are more than 100 children of the neighborhood who attend this daycare center. Children of the center are between the ages of 11 months to 6 years.  At this daycare they can receive education, food and recreation, as well as information about hygiene, health and citizenship. The daycare also promotes integration of activities with parents and the community.\r\n\r\nThis Christmas, the children wrote letters to Santa Claus asking for toys, clothes, school supplies, among other wants and needs.  The Avenue Code team in Brazil are collaborating with donations and meeting the demands of the letters.\r\n\r\nWe are asking for your cooperation so that we can meet the requests of all children (buy toys, clothes and school supplies) and make their Christmas happier and complete.\r\n\r\nWe are going to deliver all the collected gifts and also make a little party in this Daycare Center on Dec 12th. If you are in the US, you can also collaborate by donating some money though this website:http://vakinha.com.br/VaquinhaP.aspx?e=181374\r\n\r\nAll the money collected will be used to buy the gifts. Check out the daycare’s website:http://www.crecheterranova.com.br/\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Avenue Code Giving Back', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'avenue-code-giving-back', '', '', '2015-05-18 17:21:02', '2015-05-18 17:21:02', '', 0, 'http://revamp.avenuecode.com/?p=255', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(256, 1, '2012-10-17 21:32:09', '2012-10-17 21:32:09', 'Avenue Code\'s premiere networking event, TECH TIME, finally happened Tuesday evening,\r\n\r\nOctober 9th, at the Hub. Top-tier talent from various industries such as: retail, IT, and finance were in attendance. The room was packed and there was an air of excitement as individuals had the opportunity to mingle with fellow IT professionals. Here are some highlights from the event!\r\n\r\n<a href="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-179" src="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01-300x198.png" alt="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01.png" width="300" height="198" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe MC of the event was the one of Avenue Code\'s outstanding employees and the president of the San Francisco Bay Area Chapter of Project Management Institute Elaine Law, who opened the event with a welcome message. Then Cloud Evangelist, Jim Ash , from HP Cloud shared the reasons to migrate to a public cloud and future capabilities of HP’s public cloud. Avenue Code was pleased to have HP Cloud sponsor the event.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/02.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-180" src="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/02-300x198.png" alt="02" width="300" height="198" /></a><a href="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/03.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-181" src="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/03-300x198.png" alt="03" width="300" height="198" /></a>\r\n\r\nSoon after, Zeo Solomon gave a presentation on the Omni-channel.  His speech was inspiring and brought a comedic angle to the evening\'s event. Zeo\'s genius analogy of the "18th camel", --which implied that Omni-channel technology is a magical solution for frustrations caused by having multiple channels--was repeated throughout the rest of the event.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/04.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-182" src="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/04-300x198.png" alt="04" width="300" height="198" /></a>\r\n\r\nZeo\'s presentation was the perfect segue into the panel discussion, which was moderated by Elaine Law. Avenue Code was honored to have a great set of panel guests: Kari Friedman, Chip Overstreet, and Lance Wills. They brought valuable experience and hands-on market insights to the table and updated the attendees on what retail stores have been doing with the integration of multiple channels of revenue steam.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/05.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-183" src="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/05-300x198.png" alt="05" width="300" height="198" /></a>\r\n\r\nThere was great interest from the crowd in hearing the panel guests. Some of the audience members raised critical questions on how to integrate different channels seamlessly. Even after the 50 minute panel session, people lingered around to discuss more about the possibility of the new technology. From this, we can confidently say that Avenue Code\'s Tech Time ended successfully!\r\n\r\n<a href="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/07.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-185" src="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/07-300x198.png" alt="07" width="300" height="198" /></a> <a href="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/06.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-184" src="http://avenuecode.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/06-300x198.png" alt="06" width="300" height="198" /></a>\r\n\r\nHopefully you will join us next time.  The next Tech Time topic and date will be announced soon. For those who came, thank you very much. See you at the next Tech Time!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'October\'s Tech Time Recap', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'octobers-tech-time-recap', '', '', '2015-05-18 17:21:15', '2015-05-18 17:21:15', '', 0, 'http://revamp.avenuecode.com/?p=256', 0, 'post', '', 0),
